S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
AMENDING THE RULES OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES FOR THE YEARS
2023 AND 2024
Introduced By: Representative Brian C. Newberry
Date Introduced: January 10, 2025
Referred To: House Rules
1 RESOLVED, That section 12 of the rules of the House of Representatives adopted by the
2 House of Representatives at its January session A.D. 2023, entitled "House Resolution Adopting
3 the Rules of the House of Representatives for the years 2023 and 2024", be and the same is
4 hereby amended to read as follows;
5 (n) A committee shall only take testimony on a bill if the bill sponsor or another member
6 of the House is present to formally present the bill to the committee. Provided, however, this rule
7 shall not apply to any town or city bill. This provision may be waived at the discretion of the
8 committee chair.
